      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLYING SHELBY (2) missed the placings two starts back then ran a better race and finished 2 lengths away in fourth last time out over 1600m at Hamilton. Best figures measure up nicely. Sure to run well. WAR NO MORE (7) has been in the placings at his last two starts, finishing second last time over 1600m at Hamilton. Likely to be about the mark again. HEMI TWO BARRELL (4) gets to 1600m on debut, which is always a tough assignment, but has shown glimpses at the jumpouts and this isn't the strongest race. FRENCH COURT (8) is a seven-start maiden who finished fifth after being in the firing line on the bend at her most recent appearance over 2100m at Ballarat Synthetic. Likely to be in the finish in this suitable assignment. GASOLINE RAINBOW (9) showed good early dash and led for much of the way before weakening out of it when 7 lengths away in sixth over 1443m at Geelong. Among the main hopes.",
